Personnel of the Lekki Concession Centre, including some other persons within the vicinity, on Wednesday morning, prevented a man from jumping the bridge into the lagoon on suicide mission in Lagos. The man chose a lonely location on the Lekki -Ikoyi link bridge on Wednesday morning to jump into the lagoon but was restrained by the urgent intervention of the rescuers, Patrol officers of the Lekki Concession Centre and other bystanders.
The man was later handed over to security operatives.
